@node INTRODUCTION "Introduction"
@{" " link INHOUD}
                            @{b}I N T R O D U C T I O N
                            -----------------------@{ub}

  The Rulings Summaries for Magic: The Gathering (TM), a Collectable Card Game
  by @{"Wizards of the Coast" link WOTC}, are just normal textfiles and have no links
  whatsoever to each other. @{"Stephen D'Angelo" link STEPHEN_D'ANGELO} is doing a great job putting
  the rulings together each month.

  So to make things easy for you, this Guide was made, first by @{b}Tom de Ruyter@{ub}
  and now by us.

  We hope you enjoy it.
  
  @{"The authors" link The_authors}

@endnode
@node FEEDBACK "Please let us know that you're alive !"
@{" " link INHOUD}
                    @{b}Please let us know that you're alive !@{ub}
                    --------------------------------------


  Please take some time to answer the following questions.

  1. How do you normally obtain the latest release of the MTG Guide ?
     - FTP
     - WEB
     - Other (please specify)

  2. How many times do you read the MTG Guide ?
     - Every day
     - Once a week
     - Once a month
     - Only when I need to know a certain ruling/card description
     - Never (I use it to fill my harddisk with useless information)

  3. What is your computer configuration ?

  4. What is your interest in the CCG of Magic: The Gatering ?
     - I'm mostly a player
     - I'm mostly a collector
     - I'm both a player and collector

  5. Would you like to be informed (by email) about the new releases ?
     - Yes (send us your email address)
     - No

  6. If you have any ideas to improve the MTG Guide, please let us know.



  Please send your answers and suggestions or comments you have to our
  email-address at: @{b}enrgizer@tref.nl@{ub}


  @{" Thanks ! " link INHOUD}

@endnode
@node COPYRIGHT "Copyright"
@{" " link INHOUD}
                             @{b}Copyright and credits@{ub}
                             ---------------------

  @{fg highlight}@{b}CONTENTS@{ub}@{fg text}
  --------
  All  the rulings are collected by @{"Stephen D'Angelo" link STEPHEN_D'ANGELO} and produced in two text
  files  which  are distributed once a month.  He should take all the credits
  for the contents of these text files.

  Most of the card  descriptions are taken  from  the socalled "Devjoes List"
  (version 7.0)  which is  distributed  irregularry by  @{"Joseph W. DeVincentis" link DEVINCENTIS}
  on the Internet.

  Descriptions  for  Alliances  &  Mirage  were taken from the Spoiler Lists,
  which  were  distributed  on the Internet by Neutral Ground, a store in New
  York/USA.   This company has it's own homepage (http://www.nground.com) and
  can be reached by Email at info@nground.com.

  Descriptions  for Visions, Fifth Edition, Weatherlight, Portal and Tempest
  were  taken  from the Spoiler Lists, which are distributed on the Internet
  by Wizards of the Coast themselves.

  Flavor Texts for Homelands, Alliances & Mirage were taken from my own cards.
  All others came directly from a homepage on the Internet.

  All  other  information,  like  the  "Reserved  List" are taken from either
  articles in Magazines like The Duelist (TM) and Scrye (TM) or directly from
  text files distributed on the Internet.

  @{fg highlight}@{b}FORMAT & ERRORS@{ub}@{fg text}
  ---------------
  We,  @{"The authors" link THE_AUTHORS}, take the credits for the Amiga Guide format.  Any errors
  introduced  in  the  text files, during re-formatting them into Amiga Guide
  format, are us to blame and nobody else.


  @{fg highlight}@{b}COPYRIGHT, TRADEMARKS, DISCLAIMERS & LEGAL MUMBO JUMBO@{ub}@{fg text}
  ------------------------------------------------------
  WIZARDS OF THE COAST and MAGIC: THE GATHERING are registered
  trademarks of @{"Wizards of the Coast" link WOTC}.

  Arabian Nights TM, Antiquities TM, Legends TM, The Dark TM,
  Fallen Empires TM, Ice Age TM, Chronicles TM, Homelands TM,
  Alliances TM, Mirage TM, Visions TM, Weatherlight TM,Portal TM,
  Tempest, Pocket Player's Guide TM are trademarks of
  Wizards of the Coast, Inc.

  @{fg highlight}@{b}THIS PRODUCT IS NOT PUBLISHED OR ENDORSED BY WIZARDS OF THE COAST, INC. (TM)@{ub}@{fg text}

@endnode
