@endnode
@node DISTRIBUTION "How to get the latest update"
@{" " link INHOUD}

                      @{b}Where to obtain the latest version@{ub}
                      ----------------------------------

There are several ways to get the latest update of these texts/rulings.

  @{b}AMIGA GUIDE FORMAT@{ub}
  ------------------
  WWW: @{b}http://leden.tref.nl/enrgizer/@{ub}

  FTP: @{b}pub/aminet/docs/misc/@{ub}MTGRUL**.LHA (** = 2 digit month number)

  BBS: @{b}+31(0)70-3680039 Neon-Noon BBS, Thanks Shai.

 
  @{b}HTML FORMAT@{ub}
  -----------
  Robert Dekker has translated the MTG Guide into HTML format, so it's now
  possible to view it with any browser you like. The whole thing is still
  in BETA phase, however if you want to check it out, please visit his
  homepage at the World Wide Web: @{b}http://people.a2000.nl/rdekker@{ub}

  @{b}NORMAL TEXT FILES@{ub}
  -----------------
  FTP: Connect to @{b}ftp.itis.com@{ub} and look under "pub/deckmaster/rules/" for
       "rule-*.txt" to get a copy.

       Connect to @{b}ftp.activesw.com@{ub} and look under "pub/sdangelo/magic/" for
       "rule-*.txt" to get a copy.

  WWW: @{b}http://www.activesw.com/~sdangelo/magic.html@{ub}


  Both the Amiga Guide files and the normal text files versions are freely
  redistributable. Spread the word !!

@endnode
